article.headline: George Mason 79, Duquesne 58
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. (AP) -- Tony Skinn had 23 points, eight assists and five rebounds to lead George Mason to a 79-58 victory over Duquesne on Saturday night. Jai Lewis had 20 points and 11 rebounds for the Patriots (2-1). Lamar Butler added 19 points and five assists. Skinn shot 8-for-17 from the field, including 5-for-8 on 3-pointers. Butler was 5-for-12 from 3-point range against the Dukes, who played zone defense throughout. DeVario Hudson had 18 points to lead Duquesne (1-5), which has lost four in a row. Kieron Achara added 15 points and 11 rebounds. Skinn made four 3-pointers in the first half, including a buzzer-beater for a 41-23 halftime lead. Butler scored 10 points in the first half for the Patriots, who shot 7-for-16 from behind the arc in the period.
